From 5505a0218958d436eecf0e4631f158bb70a453ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 08:57:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Walkthrough clips keep mic audio, exported form no longer
 truncated, Gemini Live enabled, Nova Sonic connects
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- use-live-agent: pass the live session mic stream into CameraCapture.record —
  the plumbing landed last commit but the call site never used it, so recording
  grabbed a second (silent on iOS Safari/Android) mic track: soundless clips.
  Verified end-to-end that the uploaded clip's opus audio track survives
  take_video -> /api/inspection/video -> saved file -> form embed -> export.
- inspection.html exportHtml: the strip-previous-state regex matched its own
  quoted source and lazily ate everything to the file's final </script>,
  leaving the main script unclosed — browsers drop unclosed scripts, so every
  exported form (the file shipped to Slack) opened dead. Anchored the regex to
  a real boot script ("= {") and switched the boot insertion to a replacer
  function so $-sequences in notes can't corrupt the doc. Verified in-browser:
  exact notes, photos, and the audio-bearing video rehydrate from the export.
- agent: Gemini Live (gemini-3.1-flash-live-preview) enabled in the provider
  registry — appears in /api/models and connects via /ws.
- requirements: add aws-sdk-bedrock-runtime — BidiNovaSonicModel imports
  aws_sdk_bedrock_runtime, which was never installed, so every Nova session
  died at model construction (ModuleNotFoundError). README notes the
  Python 3.12+ floor the Nova provider enforces.
- main: create_agent moved inside the websocket try block so construction
  failures reach the browser as bidi_error instead of a silent dead socket
  (this is why Nova "wouldn't connect" with no visible reason).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01RAA1vKwXKSMRyuFaq6SwKV
